Class User

java.lang.Object
dat.backend.model.entities.User
public class User extends Object
This class contains all the data that represents a user of the application, including methods that alters the user's information.

  • Constructor Details

    • User

      public User(int userID, String email, String password, String name, int phoneNumber, String address, String role)
      This constructor is used after login confirmation.
      Parameters:
      userID - user's id number - generated by the database.
      email - user's email - required to log on the application.
      password - user's password for the application.
      name - Customer's full name - contact information.
      phoneNumber - Customer's phone number - contact information.
      address - Customer's real life address - contact information.
      role - admin/user

    • User

      public User(int userID, String email, String password, String name, int phoneNumber, String address, String role, ConnectionPool connectionPool)
      This constructor is only used for test-purposes.
      Parameters:
      userID - user's id number - generated by the database.
      email - user's email - required to log on the application.
      password - user's password for the application.
      name - Customer's full name - contact information.
      phoneNumber - Customer's phone number - contact information.
      address - Customer's real life address - contact information.
      role - admin/user
      connectionPool - required to make connection to the database
